BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zxaFwMuE5cxpv8egXbpgj
SUMMARY:Member Family Day: Animal Intelligence
DTSTAMP:20260411T040859Z
DTSTART:20260411T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:SAM members\, don't have a room with a view booked this spring 
	break? Kick off your staycation with A Room for Animal Intelligence. Get y
	our free tickets to visit the museum on April 11 \\(or anytime through Apr
	il 19\\) and enjoy enriching activities. This is a whole new way of seeing
	 the animal world curated by Pam McClusky. Come face-to-face with 100 anim
	als from around the globe\, rendered at jaw- dropping scale. We're talking
	 the largest wolf\, mouse\, and mosquito you've ever laid eyes on. The kid
	s won't stop talking about it-and honestly\, neither will you. Grab a bite
	 from the Shooby Doo pop-up café \\(11 am-3 pm\\)\, listen to live jazz cu
	rated by Seattle Jazz Fellowship \\(11 am-2 pm\\)\, and join a public coll
	ection tour that includes a stop in A Room for Animal Intelligence \\(11:3
	0 am\\). 10 am-5 pm Build a Beast Brotman Forum Build your very own beast 
	using hand-carved animal stamps created by artist Brian Lane. Pen Pal with
	 an Animal A Room for Animal Intelligence gallery Choose your favorite ani
	mal in the exhibition to be pen pals with and write to them using the stat
	ionary provided in the gallery. Who knows! You might just hear back . . . 
	Wolf Haven International Booth Brotman Forum Visit the Wolf Haven Internat
	ional booth to learn more about wolves and the organization's efforts to r
	estore near-extinct species. Animal-themed Scavenger Hunt A Room for Anima
	l Intelligence Pick up a scavenger hunt created by SAM Docent\, David Turn
	er\, from the Ticketing Desk and embark on your adventure to discover the 
	wit\, wonder\, and wisdom of A Room for Animal Intelligence! 10:30 am | Co
	mplimentary Pastries for Members Arnold Board Room Start your morning with
	 a delicious pastry made by Shooby Doo Catering \\(while supplies last\\).
	 11-11:30 am | Illustrated Storytime with Julie Kim Arnold Board Room Brin
	g your little one to experience the artistic magic of an illustrated anima
	l storytime by artist Julie Kim. 11:30 am-noon | Selfies with Sammy the Ca
	mel A Room for Animal Intelligence gallery Step into the gallery after sto
	rytime to take a selfie with Sammy the Camel! 1-1:30 pm | Wolves 101 Talk 
	Arnold Board Room Learn all about wolves from a globally recognized wolf s
	anctuary\, Wolf Haven International\, at this engaging talk for kids! 3-4 
	pm | Wolves in the Pacific Northwest Talk Arnold Board Room Learn all abou
	t wolves of the Pacific Northwest and what it takes to restore near-extinc
	t populations from Wolf Haven International. Sun Apr 12-Sun Apr 19 Can't m
	ake the kick-off event on April 11? Visit any open day during spring break
	 week to write to an animal\, build a beast and go on a scavenger hunt. Pl
	us\, curator Pam McClusky will be leading a few short tours of the exhibit
	ion \\(3 pm on Apr 15\, 16 and 17\\) and all public tours that week will s
	top in A Room for Animal Intelligence.  These activities are free to membe
	rs and 40% off admission for your guests! Simply reserve museum tickets fo
	r April 11. Or visit between the 12 and 19 to celebrate A Room for Animal 
	Intelligence with us.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/mem
	ber-family-day-animal-intelligence/18529573/2026-04-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday
	 - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/member-family-day-animal-
	intelligence/18529573/2026-04-11T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
