BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zp8NL2gg4kd8-owgtZlXQ
SUMMARY:Housing Justice: From Policy to Practice
DTSTAMP:20260411T040901Z
DTSTART:20260424T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join YWCA Seattle | King | Snohomish for Housing Justice: From 
	Policy to Practice\, a virtual panel focusing on the ways housing policies
	 show up in real life. We will explore what's working and what's not\, and
	 the changes needed to ensure safe\, stable\, and affordable housing for a
	ll people across King and Snohomish Counties.\n\nHear from a group of comm
	unity leaders\, advocates\, and service providers\, as they ground the con
	versation in local context\, share the realities of implementation\, and e
	levate solutions that center equity\, accountability\, lived experience\, 
	and community voice.\n\nFeatured speakers for this event are:\n\n- Gregory
	 Davis\, Rainier Beach Action Coalition\n\n- Colleen Echohawk\, Community 
	Roots Housing\n\n- Alison Eisinger\, Seattle/King County Coalition on Home
	lessness\n\n- Estela Ortega\, El Centro de la Raza\n\n- Mindy Woods\, Snoh
	omish County Human Services \\(facilitator\\)\n\nAbout Until Justice Just 
	Is\n\nThis year marks the 15th anniversary of this annual event\, formerly
	 known as Stand Against Racism and hosted by the People of Color Executive
	 Council of YWCA Seattle | King | Snohomish.\n\nA signature campaign of YW
	CA USA Until Justice Just Is invites communities across the country to com
	e together with YWCA to raise awareness about the impacts of racism and to
	 build community among those working for racial justice.\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/housing-justice-from-policy-to-practice/18
	524086/2026-04-24T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/housing-justice-from-poli
	cy-to-practice/18524086/2026-04-24T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_B0Kv-BGlW3dKfqNsgltR
SUMMARY:Decay
DTSTAMP:20260411T040901Z
DTSTART:20260424T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Decay explores how we navigate and engage with the inevitable e
	ntropy of our world.\n\nThis exhibition shows us the joy of degeneration\,
	 the beauty of collapse\, the peace that comes from crumbling into dust. T
	he work\, primarily from Pacific Northwest artists\, ranges from sculptura
	l\, to wall-mounted 3D\, video and installation works. Included in this ex
	hibition will be works created using natural and reclaimed materials\, as 
	well as pieces designed to create spaces for quiet reflection on the theme
	. Decay appears as part of the natural world and in our bodies in many for
	ms\, and so over the duration of the show\, some works may change over tim
	e\, exemplifying the theme. Many of the pieces prompt reflection on mortal
	ity\, the fragility of the physical body and the sacred.\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/decay/18493748/2026-04-24T00\n\nFrom SEAto
	day - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/decay/18493748/2026-04-24
	T00
LOCATION:The Vestibule\, 5919 15th Ave. N.W.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8uavDbyZTaVR3c4WASzVH
SUMMARY:Scott Gibson - Visual Symphony II
DTSTAMP:20260411T040901Z
DTSTART:20260424T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:In March\, Visual Symphony II Scott Gibson invites viewers into
	 a world where music and art collide. Each work is an exploration of the v
	ivid\, sensory experience of sound translating into vibrant\, emotional vi
	suals. As an artist with synesthesia each work expresses Scott’s personal 
	perception of what music looks like. Scott uses resin techniques that he h
	as pioneered and pushes the boundaries of this medium.\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symphony-ii/18280602/202
	6-04-24T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symph
	ony-ii/18280602/2026-04-24T00
LOCATION:Gray Sky Gallery\, 320 First Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
